Class Device

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.upv.grc.grcbox.server.networkInterfaces.Device

  • class Device
extends java.lang.Object
    The Class Device, only used in NetworkInterfaceManager to store devices related to NetworkManager DBus interfaces

    • Constructor Detail

      • Device

        public Device(java.lang.String dbusPath,
              java.lang.String iface,
              org.freedesktop.dbus.UInt32 ifaceIpAddress,
              org.freedesktop.dbus.UInt32 capabilities,
              org.freedesktop.dbus.UInt32 state,
              java.lang.String activeConnectionPath,
              java.lang.String ip4ConfigPath,
              boolean managed,
              org.freedesktop.dbus.UInt32 type)
        Instantiates a new device.
        Parameters:
        dbusPath - the dbus path
        iface - the iface name
        ifaceIpAddress - the iface ip address
        capabilities - the capabilities of the device as defined by NM
        state - the state of the device as defined by NM
        activeConnectionPath - the active connection path
        ip4ConfigPath - the ip4 config path
        managed - true if the device is managed by NM
        type - the type of the interface WIRED or WIRELESS
